  { question: "What factors affect loan interest rates?", answer: "Loan interest rates are influenced by your credit score, income and debt-to-income ratio, loan amount and term, collateral (secured vs. unsecured), current market conditions, and the type of loan. Higher credit scores and shorter loan terms generally qualify for lower rates." },
